results.title: Avengers (1963) #260
results.description: The outer space battle rages on between the Avengers, Nebula, the Skrulls, and Thanos! The mysterious and twisted secret of Nebula revealed. How did the daughter of Thanos become the most merciless, ruthless woman in the galaxy?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #261
results.description: The Avengers retreat from space following the aftermath of the battle between Nebula and the Skrulls. Cap contemplates the Beyonder’s arrival to earth, and questions his motives.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #262
results.description: The Avengers check out a hydro-base belonging to Sting-Ray, after the FAA prevents the team from launching Quinjets at the mansion. Namor shows up during the tour in a foul mood, but is in better spirits after a duel with Hercules. Cap offers Namor a spot on the Avengers roster, and the prickly king of Atlantis happily accepts! Namor’s introductory issue as member of the Avengers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #263
results.description: Captain America, Wasp, and Black Knight must convince their federal sponsor, Raymond Sikorsky, that Namor is a worthy candidate for full membership. While observing the Wasp during a training session, Black Knight wonders if she might want to date him.

results.title: What Lurks Below?
results.description: Sub-Mariner joins the Avengers; The Avengers retrieve a cocoon from the bottom of Jamaica Bay which contains the dormant body of the long-thought-dead Jean Grey of X-Men fame.

items.name: Fantastic Four Visionaries: John Byrne Vol. 7 (2007)
Fantastic Four Visionaries: John Byrne Vol. 7 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Avengers (1963) #264
results.description: Black Knight makes it a priority to study the erratic spikes in Wasp’s powers. Meanwhile, a young woman steals Hank Pym’s Yellowjacket suit and makes her own deadly modifications.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #265
results.description: Captain America’s suspicions about the Beyonder prove accurate, when he is held prisoner by the villain in a mountain cave. Tossed into the Beyonder’s energy tornado, Captain Marvel, Black Knight, Namor, and Hercules attempt to collect their bearings and find Cap before it’s too late! The Beyonder promises to unleash his fury against the Avengers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #266
results.description: Silver Surfer joins the battle against the Beyonder in the Rocky Mountains! But when the Surfer realizes that this battle threatens the cosmic balance, the Avengers must improvise a new plan to save the planet.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #267
results.description: Kang has almost eliminated all the time divergent duplicates created each time he jumped through time. Meanwhile, the public protests Namor's membership with the Avengers. The Wasp, Black Knight and Hercules are transported to Limbo by Kang where he hopes they will help him destroy the final time duplicate.

items.name: Avengers: Kang Time and Time Again (2005)
Avengers: Kang Time and Time Again (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Avengers (1963) #268
results.description: Captain Marvel, Namor, and Captain America investigate the disappearance of their teammates. From the beginning, however, Captain America suspects Kang. The rest of the team makes it to Limbo, but will it be too late for kidnapped members Wasp, Black Knight and Hercules?

items.name: Avengers: Kang Time and Time Again (2005)
Avengers: Kang Time and Time Again (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Avengers (1963) #269
results.description: While Kang gloats over his captive Avengers, the unengaged members attack. The team manages to flee the clutches of Kang, and convince Immortus to send them back to their rightful time and place.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #270
results.description: WILD IN THE STREETS! Prince Namor, aka The Sub-Mariner, has joined The Avengers and the public isn't happy about it! Sensing an opportunity to attack, Moonstone makes her move! Featuring Absorbing Man and Titania.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #271
results.description: BREAKAWAY! It's Wasp and Paladin against The Grey Gargoyle! Meanwhile, supervillains are being sprung from prisons all over the country! Featuring Black Knight, Captain America, Captain Marvel, and Hercules!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #272
results.description: RITES OF CONQUEST! Baron Zemo is hell bent on destroying the Avengers once and for all! The Masters of Evil have stormed The Avengers Mansion and there's only one person home: Jarvis!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #273
results.description: DIVIDED WE FALL! The Masters of Evil have claimed The Avengers Mansion as their own! What will happen to The Earth's Mightiest when they return to their HQ? The Black Knight is about to find out!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #275
results.description: EVEN A GOD CAN DIE! The Masters of Evil have nearly killed Hercules! As The Wasp rushes to Lion of Olympus' side, Baron Zemo sends Crusher Creel and Titania to finish the job!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #278
results.description: She-Hulk pays a long overdue visit to the Avengers Hydrobase, but her arrival coincides with an attack from Tyrak! Following the battle, Wasp nominates Dr. Druid for Avengers membership and steps down as chairwoman to take a formal leave of absence.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #279
results.description: Doctor Druid decides to join the Avengers! Following Wasp’s departure, Captain America offers young Captain Marvel the position of chairwoman. After deliberating amongst herself and her family, Captain Marvel accepts!

results.title: The Coming of the Accursed Avengers
Avengers (1963) #301
results.description: The new Avengers decide to set up permanent shop at the Hydrobase in New York Harbor. But just as team settles into their new digs, a galactic threat from Nebula arrives!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #302
results.description: Super-Nova is plummeting towards Earth seeking vengeance against Nebula. However, little does he know, Nebula has been lost in the time stream. The East Coast Avengers must placate an angry Super-Nova until the West Coast team arrives to save the day.
